description: From New Latin cellulāris, from cellula (“cell”) + -āris.

adjectives.description: cellular (comparative more cellular, superlative most cellular)

entries.meaning: Of, relating to, consisting of, or resembling a cell or cells.

examples: MULDER: Yeah, Eddie, this is all good stuff. Yeah, see what else you can find on him from the N.C.I.C. and call me back. At, at this number or on my cellular.
